<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Pickett; Playwright Dealt With AIDS Issues 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Pickett, 44, playwright who was a co-founder of Artists Confronting 
AIDS.Pickett's best-known plays were "Bathhouse Benediction," "Dream Man" and 
"Queen of Angels," all dealing with homosexuality in the era of AIDS. He was 
among the first to organize a series of presentations featuring gay writers at 
a bookstore, choosing A Different Light in West Hollywood. On Monday in Los 
Angeles of AIDS. 
</P>
