<TEXT>
<P>
 The view from the field did not show how seriously Tab Ramos was injured 
during Monday's 1-0 loss to Brazil.Players and coaches saw Ramos elbowed in the 
head by Brazil's Leonardo and fall to the ground, but they couldn't gauge the 
extent of his injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramos was taken from the field semi-conscious, and U.S. Coach Bora Milutinovic 
asked him at halftime if he was ready to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramos' childhood friend, John Harkes, said he watched the replay and only then 
fully understood the visciousness of the blow. 
</P>
<P>
 "Literally, I almost got sick," Harkes said. "His legs kicked out from under 
him. It's a sad way to go out of the World Cup." JULIE CART 
