</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sun in London reported its switchboard lit up when British TV commentator 
Kevin Keegan, a star for Liverpool and England as a player and now manager of 
the Newcastle club, said of the elbowing of Ramos: "It didn't look like such a 
bad challenge to me." 
</P>
<P>
 As Ramos was carried off on a stretcher and Leonardo shown a red card, Keegan 
added: "It didn't look like he did that much wrong to me.Maybe it's my eyes. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm disappointed to see Leonardo, who I considered to be the best player in 
the World Cup, going off for one moment of madness." 
</P>
<P>
 His view was greatly in the minority. One typical caller to The Sun declared: 
"That's not the sort of comment we expect from an ambassador of the game." 
