<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: SEVERAL LUNKER TROUT ESCAPE HOLIDAY CRUNCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Most of the Alpers trout planted in Eastern Sierra waters before the July 4 
weekend escaped the onslaught of holiday fishermen. That's good news for future 
anglers, because the already large fish will grow even larger. 
</P>
<P>
 Among those that didn't escape: a seven-pound five-ounce rainbow caught on a 
Panther Martin lure by Colter Taylor of Vista at Lake Sabrina above Bishop; a 
five-pounder caught by 5-year-old Brianne Codeus of Upland on a glob of Power 
Bait at Grant Lake on the June Loop and a 4-12 fish landed by Lloyd Scott of 
Palm Springs, on Power Bait at June Lake. 
</P>
