BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MINORS / MAJORS; ANOTHER HOME RUN FOR 
STRAWBERRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Darryl Strawberry made another successful step in his comeback when he hit his 
second home run in as many games for the triple-A Phoenix Giants. 
</P>
<P>
 Strawberry, attempting to play himself back into shape after sitting out all 
of the regular season while undergoing substance-abuse treatment, homered in 
the third inning against Vancouver left-hander Andrew Lorraine at Scottsdale, 
Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 Strawberry had a sacrifice fly in the first and a solo shot in the third that 
landed in the right field bullpen. 
</P>
<P>
 New York Yankee first baseman and team captain Don Mattingly was placed on the 
15-day disabled list because of tendinitis in his right wrist. . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Baseball players are expected to present their opening contract demands when 
negotiations for a new collective bargaining agreement resume today. 
