By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 30-year-old Ventura woman is scheduled to be arraigned today after she was 
arrested on suspicion of trying to kidnap a 2-year-old boy from his mother's 
side at a crowded holiday street fair. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly Young was being held at Ventura County Jail on $20,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura police said Young allegedly tried to take William Goins at about 4:25 
p.m. at Oak and Santa Clara streets in downtown Ventura on Monday. The toddler 
