<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; WOMAN, 66, KILLED IN CAR COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON GRANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 66-year-old Moorpark woman was killed in a traffic collision Tuesday morning 
when she pulled out of her mobile-home park and was struck broadside by a van, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Elinor Foster, a resident of the Villa Del Arroyo Mobile Home Park, was struck 
about 6:25 a.m. by an oncoming van driven by Charles McLaughlin, 41, of 
Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 The van was traveling east on Old Los Angeles Avenue toward Simi Valley, 
Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. Keith Parks said. 
</P>
<P>
 "At this juncture, it appears that she pulled out in front of the oncoming 
van," Parks said. 
</P>
<P>
 But Parks said that an investigation into the accident is continuing and that 
no arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 Traffic on Old Los Angeles Avenue was backed up for three hours as a result of 
the accident, Parks said.  
</P>
<P>
 Parks said Pruner Ambulance and Ventura County Fire Department personnel 
pulled Foster from her car after the accident. She was pronounced dead at 7:30 
a.m. at Simi Valley Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 McLaughlin was taken to Los Robles Regional Medical Center in Thousand Oaks 
with internal injuries and was in stable condition Tuesday, hospital officials 
said. JASON GRANT 
</P>
</TEXT>
