EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; SENIOR CENTER LIKELY TO HIRE COORDINATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark City Council is expected to accept an $8,000 grant from the 
Ventura County Area Agency on Aging to pay for a part-time coordinator at the 
city's senior center. 
</P>
<P>
 The coordinator would help Carol Ghens, director of the center.Ghens, who won 
an award from Gov. Pete Wilson for her work at the 1 1/2-year-old center, said 
she is stretched to the limit. 
</P>
<P>
 "There are so many things I need help with," Ghens said. "We have a lot of 
volunteers, but it just goes beyond what volunteers can do." 
</P>
<P>
 Christine Adams, director of the city's Community Services Department, said 
Ghens is in part a victim of her own success. The center once was seeing about 
50 people, but more than 600 use its services now. And each day new people come 
in, Adams said. 
</P>
<P>
 "She's the only paid staffer at the center," Adams said. "Another employee 
would free her to work on new ideas to make the center even better." SCOTT 
HADLY 
</P>
