EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; 3 FACE ARRAIGNMENT IN TAGGING SPREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Simi Valley men are scheduled to be arraigned today on felony charges of 
vandalism after police arrested them during a weekend graffiti spree in San 
Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 The alleged taggers, who were arrested with two others from Southern 
California, were taken into custody about 2 a.m. Sunday after San Francisco 
police responded to a complaint of graffiti, Lt. Daniel Lawson said. 
</P>
<P>
 When officers arrived on Clay Street, they saw the five in the area and some 
had paint on their hands, Lawson said. At least four buildings had been tagged 
and damages were more than $5,000, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident is unusual because taggers generally target businesses near or in 
their hometowns, Lawson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They generally just spray in their own territory," Lawson said. "This is 
somewhat unique in that their artistic license has been extended a few hundred 
miles." 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested were Kevin Martin, 18; Shawn Buss, 22, and Jesse Rosen, 22, all of 
Simi Valley. Jason Drew, 23, of Northridge and Carter Hogue, 21, of Lake 
Elsinore were also arrested. The five were being held at San Francisco County 
Jail. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
