<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; FAMILY MOVIE SERIES TO BEGIN JULY 8 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free family-oriented movies will be shown on a 12-foot outdoor screen at the 
Arovista Park Amphitheatre this summer. Sponsoring the second annual "Family 
Fridays" program are the city of Brea and the Brea Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Audience members are asked to bring blankets, picnic dinners and beach chairs 
to the screenings, which will begin at 8:15 p.m. Fridays. Snacks will be 
available for purchase, with proceeds helping support the seven-week program. 
</P>
<P>
 Beginning the series July 8 will be "Beethoven's 2nd," starring Charles 
Grodin. The screenings will continue with "The Land Before Time," July 15; "The 
Three Musketeers," July 22; "Cool Runnings," July 29; "Duck Tales: The Movie" 
and "Treasure of the Lost Lamp," Aug. 5; "Iron Will," Aug. 12, and "D2: The 
Mighty Ducks," Aug. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Arovista Park is at 500 S. Sievers Ave. Additional information is available by 
calling the city of Brea Community Services Department at (714) 990-7735. 
</P>
</TEXT>
