<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; VACATIONERS' HEALTH WOES SUBJECT OF CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vacationers can learn how to deal with medical problems while traveling abroad 
this summer through a free workshop in San Clemente on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Samaritan Medical Center physicians warn that becoming ill or having an 
accident while traveling is often serious and expensive. 
</P>
<P>
 At 7 p.m. at the hospital, at 654 Camino de los Mares, Dr. Michael Salem, 
medical director of the San Clemente Medi-Center, will offer tips on preparing 
for the unexpected while on vacation. 
</P>
<P>
 Salem will cover tropical diseases, immunizations, first aid and other 
precautions that can avoid complications if a health problem comes up during a 
vacation trip. 
</P>
<P>
 For information and registration, call (714) 489-4566.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
