<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEMORIAL SERVICES FOR FRANK SCIAROTTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Memorial services are planned tonight for Frank Sciarotta, a longtime 
Saddleback College professor and administrator who died of cancer Friday. He 
was 63. 
</P>
<P>
 Sciarotta, who retired in 1991 after 23 years of teaching, died at his Laguna 
Hills home. 
</P>
<P>
 "Those who knew Mr. Sciarotta were always impressed with his intelligence, 
dedication and high energy," Robert A. Lombardi, the district's chancellor, 
said in a memo to faculty and staff members. 
</P>
<P>
 Sciarotta, who was originally from Stuebenville, Ohio, joined the district in 
1968 as a member of the charter faculty. In addition to teaching biology at 
Saddleback College, he chaired the college's mathematics, science and 
engineering division as well as serving as associate dean of instruction and 
continuing education. He also served as dean of administration services for the 
district. 
</P>
<P>
 Sciarotta is survived by his wife, Ann; two sons Greg of Mission Viejo and 
Mike of Kansas; a daughter, Amy Worthington of Mission Viejo; and nine 
grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 Services begin at 7 p.m. at Mission Viejo Christian Church. 
</P>
</TEXT>
