<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LEISURE WORLD; CONCERT TO BENEFIT OUTREACH PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A charity group that provides emergency food and shelter to South County's 
homeless people will benefit from a jazz and swing concert at Leisure World on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Hooked on Music Program" will showcase local groups covering classic 
sounds from acts like the Andrews Sisters, the Platters, the Mills Brothers and 
the Inkspots. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost is $5 for the show, which starts at 6 p.m. in Leisure World's 
Clubhouse Three, 23822 Avenida Sevilla. Look for the Gate Three sign off 
Moulton Parkway between El Toro Road and Laguna Hills Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Performing on Sunday will be the Ferdie Furtado Quintet, the Society Swing 
Trio and Johnny Smith and the New Inkspots. The show will be the first musical 
benefit sponsored by Saddleback Community Outreach. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization provides emergency rent assistance, food and clothing, helps 
to pay utility bills and offers many other services. 
</P>
<P>
 "South County may appear to be the land of affluence, populated by people who 
live in well-kept tract and custom homes," said Jeanne Gormick, spokeswoman for 
Saddleback Community Outreach. "But these stereotypes mask the whole truth. We 
have needy people right here in our own back yard." 
</P>
<P>
 Gormick added that donations are particularly needed in the summer because 
community contributions are generally lower during the hot months. 
</P>
<P>
 To purchase tickets, make a donation to the program or volunteer, call (714) 
380-8144. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
