<P>
WOMAN, 80, KILLED IN HIT AND RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 80-year-old Sherman Oaks woman was killed Tuesday by a hit-and-run driver 
as she crossed the parking area of a small shopping plaza, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Selma Lebovitz was struck by a car identified only as a beige or tan Chevrolet 
Nova that was headed north at the time of the 3 p.m. accident, according to 
witnesses, said Officer Bill Mulvihill of the Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The mini-mall is on the southwest corner of Laurel Canyon Boulevard and Erwin 
Street, Mulvihill said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lebovitz was pronounced dead at North Hollywood Medical Center, he said. 
