<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dispensing Caps: Tired of throwing away shampoo and conditioner bottles 
because it's too hard to get the last drops out? 
</P>
<P>
 You're not alone.Wise Choice Products of Orange is producing a "Final Drop 
Dispensing Cap" that is designed to help wring the last drop out of bottles. 
The caps have wide bases that support bottles upside down -- allowing the 
contents to easily drain to the bottom. 
</P>
<P>
 The cap is designed to fit nearly all shampoo, conditioner, lotion and gel 
bottles. The cost: $9.99 plus shipping and handling for three of the caps. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the first product we've produced," said Jack L. Turley of Orange, who 
is handling marketing for the product created by his wife, Joann, and his 
son-in-law, David Millar. 
</P>
<P>
 He credited Millar, a product designer by training, with refining Joann 
Turley's idea. 
</P>
