<P>
 Furon Co.: The company said Tuesday that it has been awarded a contract, 
valued at $4 million, by Boeing Co. for specialized aircraft components.Work 
will be completed by Furon's advanced components division in Seattle.  
</P>
<P>
 The three-year contract is for the production of ducts in the Boeing 737 
aircraft. It complements two contracts valued at more than $14 million that 
were awarded last year. The ducts deliver heating and air-conditioning service 
for the aircraft's fuselage, and are manufactured from newly designed 
composites that replace rigid foam components. Furon is based in Laguna Niguel. 
