90'S FAMILY; NEED MORE INFORMATION? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN JAQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With more than 100 breeds in the United States, selecting a dog can be a 
daunting task. For information on finding and caring for a pet, here are some 
resources: 
</P>
<P>
 American Kennel Club: For a free copy of the "Responsible Dog Ownership 
Packet" and "Dog Buyers' Education Packet," write to AKC Customer Service 
Department, 5580 Centerview Drive, Raleigh, N.C. 27606. 
</P>
<P>
 Breeder Referral Representative Hotline: For the name and number of a local 
breed representative, call (900) 407-PUPS. 
</P>
<P>
 Pedigree Selectadog: To find out which breeds are best suited for a particular 
lifestyle, send for a questionnaire to 3250 E. 44th St., Vernon, Calif. 90058. 
</P>
<P>
