<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIMPSON MURDER CASE; THE GUEST HOUSE TENANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian (Kato) Kaelin, the tenant who testified Tuesday, had been living at the 
Simpson guest house on Rockingham Avenue for free since January. He is an 
actor/writer who has appeared in "Cyborg 3" and the upcoming "Savate" and 
reportedly turned down a $100,000 offer from the National Enquirer for an 
interview. GAVEL TO GAVEL 
</P>
<P>
 New York-based Court TV, a 3-year-old cable network that features 
gavel-to-gavel coverage of trials across the nation, provides the pool TV 
camera for the coverage of the courtroom. The network says it has been getting 
about 200 calls a day about the case. Court TV has about 15.2 million 
subscribers nationally. VOICE 
</P>
<P>
 "He told me he overslept, that he just got out of the shower and he'd be down 
in a minute." 
</P>
